# Repository Hygiene

Keep the project root limited to config, entry points, and documentation. Do not leave temporary or debug files where they can be accidentally committed.

## Where Things Belong

| Kind of file | Location |
|---|---|
| Unit tests (Vitest) | `tests/*.test.js` |
| End-to-end tests (Playwright) | `tests/e2e/*.spec.js` |
| Application source | `src/` |
| Debug screenshots, scratch HTML, throwaway scripts | Delete when done, or use an ignored folder (`scratch/`, `debug/`) |

## Before Finishing a Task

- Remove ad-hoc files created for debugging (screenshots, one-off HTML, scratch scripts).
- Do not add new files to the project root unless they are project config (e.g. `vite.config.js`, `package.json`) or top-level docs (`README.md`).
- If a new tool produces artifacts not already in `.gitignore`, update `.gitignore` per the gitignore-maintenance rule.

## Examples

```
# ❌ BAD: Debug screenshot left in root after chart work
spending-scale-sparkline.png

# ❌ BAD: Throwaway test script in root
test-withdrawal-scratch.js

# ✅ GOOD: Unit test in the tests folder
tests/withdrawal.test.js

# ✅ GOOD: Delete the screenshot when debugging is done
# (or save under scratch/ which is gitignored)
```
